node.text:
Di muri a secco. Fichi d'india. Botteghe artigiane. Case e chiese. Chiese e case. Di stile arabo, barocco, turco, fenicio. E cabine telefoniche (funzionanti!) inglesi. 
Di uomini nati e cresciuti in un'isoletta lunga 26 km. 
Ho visitato i templi di Gigantia, 3600-2'800 a.C, fra le più antiche strutture del genere al mondo. Ho incontrato una troupe Rai che sarei rimasta a osservare tutto il giorno. Ho visto i colori delle saline. Sono rimasta incantata dai colori della spiaggia di Calipso dove dice fosse naufragato Ulisse. Ho fatto un mini trek bellissimo giù verso le scogliere di Game of thrones. Ho seguito Mark che mi ha fatto arrampicare sulle rocce per vedere il Blue Hole. E poi mi so cucinata uova e avocado riuscendo a confondere il sale con lo zucchero🤦🏻 #gozoisland #gozo #malta🇲🇹 #unescosite #gigantia #adventure #trip #viaggiodasolaperché #island #viaggiare #calypsocaveview

Ramla Bay - view from Calypso cave made famous in Homer’s The Odyssey. The actual cave is no longer accessible to the public because it’s become unsafe but the view overlooking the largest sandy beach of the island is superb. According to Homer’s story, Ulysses was trapped here by the nymph Calypso for seven years before resuming his journey.

Today we went to see Calypso’s Cave in Gozo. Unfortunately it’s closed for tourists now but we still had a glimpse of the entrance at least. According to the local myth this is the place where Calypso (One of Oceanides sea nymphs, the daughter of the Titan god Atlas and Tethys.) kept Odysseus from returning to Ithaca after the Trojan war. Calypso saved Odysseus from the sea when he was adrift for 9 days after losing his ship. She welcomed him and fell in love with him. She wanted him to be her immortal husband by giving him eternal youth. Odysseus didn’t accept it because he was still dreaming about going back home to Ithaca and his wife. Calypso was so much in love with him that despite his wishes she hoped he would fall in love with her and kept seducing him. Eventually she succeeded and made him her lover. They stayed together in Calypsos’ beautiful cave home for 7 years before the gods intervened and  convinced her to let Odysseus go. She helped him to build a boat to take him home. She even provided him with enough food and wine for the journey and good winds. #calypso #calypsocave #calypsocaveview #calypsocavegozo #ramlabay #ramlabeach #redsandbeach #gozo #gozoisland #beatifulview #sea #mediterreneansea #mediterrenean #ramlalhamra #sandybeach #azuresea #azurewater #hiking #dayout #beautifulnature #földközitenger #caveentrance #greekmithology #odysseus #odyssey #homer #modernhousewifewithra #tengerpart #mutimerrejarsz #mutimerrejársz
